Application Policy for Andrei Image Forum

Last Updated: 1/28/2025

1. Introduction
Welcome to Andrei Image Forum (referred to as "the Platform"). This Platform is designed to enable users to upload, share, and engage with images in a respectful and community-oriented environment. By accessing or using the Platform, you agree to adhere to this policy and the accompanying terms of service.

If you have any questions, concerns, or feedback about this policy, please contact us at: dusqcomputer@gmail.com.

2. Community Guidelines
To maintain a positive and inclusive environment, all users must comply with the following community standards:

Respect Others: Harassment, bullying, and hate speech are strictly prohibited.
Appropriate Content: Do not upload or share content that is pornographic, violent, hateful, or otherwise inappropriate.
Original Work: Share only content you own or have explicit permission to post. Avoid infringing on copyright or intellectual property rights.
Legal Compliance: All content must adhere to local, national, and international laws.
3. Content Restrictions
The following types of content are not allowed on the Platform:

Illegal or copyrighted material without proper authorization.
Explicitly violent or sexually explicit images.
Images promoting hate speech, discrimination, or harassment.
Misleading content such as fake news or manipulated media intended to deceive.
Violating these restrictions may result in the removal of your content and/or suspension of your account.

4. User Responsibilities
Users are responsible for the content they upload and share.
Users must ensure that the content is not harmful to others or in violation of this policy.
Users must report inappropriate content or behavior to the administrators via the provided email.
5. Moderation and Enforcement
Content uploaded to the Platform is subject to review by moderators.
Content that violates the policy may be removed without notice.
Repeated violations may result in account suspension or permanent banning.
Appeals for content removal or account suspension can be submitted via email to dusqcomputer@gmail.com.
6. Privacy
The Platform respects user privacy and complies with applicable data protection laws.
For more details on how your data is handled, refer to our Privacy Policy.
7. Reporting Violations
To report a violation of this policy or other concerns, email us at dusqcomputer@gmail.com. Provide as much detail as possible, including links, screenshots, or descriptions of the issue.

8. Policy Updates
This policy may be updated periodically to ensure compliance with legal requirements and to reflect changes in the Platform. Continued use of the Platform after any updates constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.

By using Andrei Image Forum, you agree to follow this policy and contribute to a positive and safe community for everyone. Thank you for being part of our forum!
